# Code ownership for the OSS public repo.
#
# The maintainer is the single owner today. CODEOWNERS rules become
# meaningful once additional collaborators are added; until then they
# serve as a "this file is critical — change it deliberately" signal.
#
# Patterns under which any change must be reviewed by the listed owner(s)
# (admin-bypass is allowed per the branch-protection rules but the rule
# still surfaces these files in the PR reviewers list automatically).

# NOTE: patterns are repo-root-relative. The crates live UNDER crates/, so every rule below
# uses the /crates/<name>/ prefix — a bare /kx-mote/ would match nothing (fixed 2026-07-06).

# ----- Repo-wide default (catch-all) -----
# Under the hardened branch protection (enforce_admins + require_code_owner_reviews +
# require_last_push_approval, 2026-07-10), a code-owner review must be meaningful for EVERY path,
# not just the specific rules below. This catch-all makes every PR require an owner review; the
# specific rules below still apply (last match wins) and simply restate the same owners.
*                                      @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Identity-bearing crates (do not change MoteDef shape lightly) -----

/crates/kx-mote/                       @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- gRPC wire contract (change additively; a break ripples to every generated client) -----

/crates/kx-proto/                      @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Capability registry (index ⟷ tree must stay consistent) ----------

/registry/                             @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- FFI boundary (unsafe-heavy; CMake/bindgen pipeline) ---------------

/crates/kx-llamacpp-sys/               @kortecx @toolexi
/crates/kx-llamacpp/                   @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Storage layer (content-addressed; atomic-per-object) --------------

/crates/kx-content/                    @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Journal (the synchronization substrate) ---------------------------

/crates/kx-journal/                    @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Projection (read-side fold over journal) --------------------------

/crates/kx-projection/                 @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- CI + governance --------------------------------------------------

/.github/workflows/                    @kortecx @toolexi
/.github/CODEOWNERS                    @kortecx @toolexi
/.github/pull_request_template.md      @kortecx @toolexi

# ----- Build orchestration ----------------------------------------------

/justfile                              @kortecx @toolexi
/Cargo.toml                            @kortecx @toolexi
/Cargo.lock                            @kortecx @toolexi
/rust-toolchain.toml                   @kortecx @toolexi
/clippy.toml                           @kortecx @toolexi
